plot: In a daring cat and mouse chase, will Tommy be outwitted by his enemies? And with the return of an old friend, Tommy tries to distract himself with other pursuits.

After Changretta has visited him in hospital and spared him Michael learns of the deal his mother made. The Lees ambush the Italians but Changretta escapes to remind Polly of their arrangement. Tommy, still hit by strikes, is visited by May Carleton, who discovers another of his lucrative side-lines, selling gin to Prohibition-hit America, whilst Ada takes Jessie for a drink on Tommy's behalf and Tommy himself calls on the services of Alfie Solomons.—don @ minifie-1
